   is still in its infancy. Manufacturing enterprises need to reshape their
   working model in order to sustain a competitive edge in this global
   manufacturing era. An Internet-enabled enterprise resource planning
   (ERP) is crucial to the continuous development of a manufacturing
   enterprise. Accordingly, in this paper, the authors propose an
   implementation model called Web-based Object-Oriented Model (WOOM) to
   implement an ERP system under a global perspective, which provides the
